The
employer
must
consider
any
increase
in
cost
that
enters
into
the
manufacture
of
his
product.
Unless
he
includes
such
cost
in
his
selling
price,
he
is
unlikely
to
show
a
profit.
The
installation
of
a
cost
system
that
enables
the
employer
to
break
down
his
costs
to
a
unit
basis
is
a
prime
necessity.
